  "body": "It would really help if we could use the `async` version of the `React.renderToString` when rendering on the server-side.\n\n``` js\napp.get('*', function (req, res) {\n\n  Router.run(routes, req.path, (Handler, router) => {\n    // var content = React.renderToString(<Handler/>);\n    // res.render('index', { content: content });\n    React.renderToString(<Handler/>, function(content) {\n      res.render('index', { content: content });\n    });\n});\n```\n",
